document: Employees must adhere to the company code of conduct at all times.
All employees are required to maintain confidentiality of sensitive information.
The company follows a hybrid work policy with three in-office days per week.
Employees are entitled to 20 days of paid leave per year excluding public holidays.
Any form of workplace harassment will result in strict disciplinary action.
Employees must inform their manager before taking planned leave.
Performance reviews are conducted twice a year for all full-time employees.
Company laptops should only be used for official work purposes.
Employees must report security incidents to the IT team immediately.
All user passwords must be at least twelve characters long.
Two-factor authentication is mandatory for all internal systems.
Access to production systems is restricted to authorized personnel only.
Source code must be stored in the company-approved version control system.
Employees should lock their systems when away from their desks.
External storage devices are not allowed without IT approval.
All software installations require prior authorization from the IT department.
All backend services are built using FastAPI and Python.
Vector embeddings are generated using large language models.
ChromaDB is used as the vector database for semantic search.
API responses must follow a consistent JSON structure.
All code changes must go through peer review before merging.
Unit tests are mandatory for all new features.
Continuous integration runs tests on every pull request.
Production deployments require approval from the tech lead.
Yash works as a backend engineering intern.
Siddhi is part of the data science team.
Eshan focuses on machine learning and artificial intelligence.
Yash and Eshan collaborate on backend infrastructure projects.
Siddhi analyzes data pipelines and builds predictive models.
The engineering team follows agile development practices.
The main office is located in Pune, India.
Yash works from the Wagholi office location.
Eshan frequently works remotely from Kondhwa.
Siddhi prefers working from the Nagar office.
Team meetings are conducted both online and in person.
Employees are encouraged to upskill through internal training programs.
Machine learning workshops are conducted every quarter.
Interns receive mentorship from senior engineers.
The company supports certification programs for employees.
Knowledge sharing sessions are held every Friday.
All employees must comply with applicable data protection laws.
Customer data should never be shared with unauthorized parties.
Ethical use of artificial intelligence is strictly enforced.
Bias and fairness must be considered when building AI systems.
Regulatory compliance is reviewed annually by the legal team.
